d super operator qwiki d super operator from qwiki jump to navigation search read the dee superoperator is often refered to as the decoherance superoperator or the lindblad superoperator the action of this operator on a state  is the lindblad superoperator describes the effect of coupling to a markovian reservoir when only the system is to be modeled dynamically while useful for modeling a range of decoherence phenomena the superoperator can only be used when bath correlations can be neglected ie bath correlations decay rapidly in comparison to system dynamics references howard wiseman thesis carmichael an open systems approach to quantum optics retrieved from http qwiki stanford edu index php d_super_operator categories concept optics quantum optics views page discussion view source history personal tools log in create account navigation main page browse categories recent changes random page community portal help faq sign up search toolbox what links here related changes special pages printable version permanent link powered by mediawiki gnu free documentation license 1.2 this page was last modified on 2 june 2007 at 04 44 this page has been accessed 11479 times content is available under gnu free documentation license 1.2 privacy policy about qwiki disclaimers
